				<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Libraries are INDEED dangerous, for the same reason it was said &#8220;the pen is mightier than the sword&#8221;. They are repositories of knowledge, and knowledge is power. Knowledge is not happiness, and protecting people from knowledge is keeping them stupid.</p>
<p> You can say that you have smart kids. But kids do not stay kids forever, and even if they are smart, without reading and writing their intelligence does little good. Libraries historically promoted literacy, and they are all going online now.  If you want to protect your kids from the internet until they are wise enough to make good decisions, consider this: Intelligence is not wisdom, and wisdom can be passed on to those willing to learn it. You cut off the tallest stalks and blades of wheat.  This way, you can tower over everyone else who is left.</p>
								</section><!-- .comment-content -->

