				<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>The ruling is what the judge has determined not Hachette. It seems many people falsely think that because something is on the Internet, it is free. Not so. If you want a hard copy of a book or magazine, most libraries will deliver a copy to your door. When you download an unauthorized  e-book, you deprive the author of his residuals, plain and simple. It&#8217;s no different than with music. No one is entitled to free use of someone&#8217;s property without expressed permission. Copyright laws exist for a reason. Obviously this is lost on many people who simply feel entitled. Try making a living from being an author, then perhaps you may wake up.</p>
								</section><!-- .comment-content -->

