				<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Genuine question: have I missed something? Libraries pay Public Lending Rights for books/ebooks that are in copyright. This is compensation to the author &amp; publisher for potential loss of sales. If IA isn’t paying public lending rights for content that is in copyright, then IA is in the wrong. If it IS paying Public Lending Rights, then the publishers are in the wrong.<br />
Fair use/freedom of information is neither here nor there in this instance.<br />
As far as I can see, IA isn’t paying PLR.<br />
Out of copyright publications shouldn’t be affected.<br />
Is there more to the action than I’ve gleaned?</p>
								</section><!-- .comment-content -->

