				<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>I am a long-time user and financial supporter of the internet Archive. According to my understanding of the origin of this lawsuit, the publishers brought suit because during the pandemic the Archive was allowing multiple loans of the same copyrighted book to multiple users at the same time. However well-intentioned, that practice of the Archive&#8217;s was sure to foment a lawsuit. The judge then went a giant step further, and in a shock addition he ruled that any single loan of a single copy to a single user at a time is a copyright infringement.  I think he is wrong there and he is wrong in saying the Archive&#8217;s lending practice is &#8220;akin to a pirate site&#8221;,</p>
								</section><!-- .comment-content -->

